<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-10T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="1097" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1097">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9660.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                    Japan</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-11T13:00:00+09:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nov. 11, 1913—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s November 7, 10 p.m.</p>
                        <p>[The Minister for Foreign Affairs being absent, the Department’s telegram
                            was communicated through the Vice-Minister for Foreign Affairs. The rest
                            of this telegram relates to information that Japan is supplying Mexico
                            with arms.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Guthrie</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>